<font face="arial,helvetica,sans serif" size="2">

<p><img src="images/main-press.jpg" width="140" height="100" vspace="5" hspace="7" alt=" [Press] " align="left">
Bjerke Forgings, Inc. was incorporated in 1988 in the State of Michigan. We supply open die
forgings, close-die forgings and rolled ring forgings to all industries. Materials range
from aluminum, alloy steel, carbon steel, copper, copper alloys, high temperature alloys steel,
stainless steel, titanium, tool steels and many other specialty steels.
<br>
<img src="images/main-hub.jpg" width="90" height="89" vspace="5" hspace="7" alt=" [Aircraft Hub] " align="right">
Forgings improve grain structure, properties, and maintain wear better than other processes
that are form from a simple casting process. We have helped many companies improve their
processes and procedures on technical issues. Our metallurgy requirements of the materials give
consistent properties based on the chemical composition and the restrictions of certain
elements.
<br>
<img src="images/main-ring.jpg" width="120" height="69" vspace="5" hspace="7" alt=" [Ring Rolling] " align="left">
Our Quality and On-Time Delivery has out-performed most of our competition. This is based on
information supplied from our customer's feedback, most of whom are customers that started with us
from the beginning and are still with us today.
</p>
</font>
